                "description": ["The South Dakota Health Education Standards includes the standards\/goals, indicators, benchmarks, and sample grade level objectives\/activities. The standards are organized into grade level clusters so that a parent, local school board member, classroom teacher, or administrator could quickly review what physical education concepts are expected at a specific grade level. Grade level clusters are organized K-2, 3-5, 6-8, and 9-12."],
