                "description": ["The Contemporary Health (9-12) curriculum was presented to the Mississippi Board of Education on September 21, 2012. Contemporary Health (9-12) is a course that develops skills related to personal, social, and mental health in today's society. It includes instruction on human growth and development, disease prevention and control, substance abuse and prevention, community and environmental health, and safety and first aid. This course is designed to satisfy the graduation requirement for health in grades 9-12."],
