                "date_valid": ["2008"],
                "description": ["The State Curriculum is the document that identifies the Maryland Content Standards and aligns them with the Maryland Assessment Program. The curriculum documents are formatted so that each begins with content standards or broad, measurable statements about what students should know and be able to do. Indicator statements provide the next level of specificity and begin to narrow the focus for teachers. Finally, the objectives provide teachers with very clear information about what specific learning should occur."],
                "identifier": ["http:\/\/asn.jesandco.org\/resources\/D10003C1", "http:\/\/purl.org\/ASN\/resources\/D10003C1"],
