                "date_modified": ["1453754565"],
                "date_valid": ["2017"],
                "description": ["Science is a way of knowing, a process for gaining knowledge and understanding of the natural world. Engineering combines the fields of science, technology, and mathematics to provide solutions to real-world problems. Students should be active learners who demonstrate their scientific understanding by using it. It is not enough for students to read about science; they must participate in the three dimensions of science. They should observe, inquire, question, formulate and test hypotheses, analyze data, report, and evaluate findings. The students, as scientists, should have hands-on, active experiences throughout the instruction of the science curriculum. These standards help students find value in developing novel solutions as they engage with complex problems."],
                "identifier": ["http:\/\/asn.desire2learn.com\/resources\/D2726259"],
                "jurisdiction": ["Utah"],
