                "description": ["The Common Core State Standards (CCSS) for Mathematics provide clear, consistent expectations about what knowledge, skills, and practices students should have and learn at each grade level so teachers and parents know what they need to do to help students achieve them. Rhode Island adopted the CCSS in Mathematics in place of a planned update to our current Grade Level Expectations (GLEs) and Grade Span Expectations (GSEs) for mathematics."],
